<a href=\"www.uudenmusiikinfestivaali.org\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Viides Uuden Musiikin Festivaali</em></a>, or \"Fifth Festival for New Music\", held in Kupittaanpuisto, Turku, Finland.\n\n<a href=\"Erotus_Records_-_Label_Launch_at_Festival_For_New_Music_5_-_25-07-2008.mp3\" target=\"_blank\">Download it</a> to hear <strong>area</strong>, <strong>asketix</strong>, <strong>blamstrain</strong>, <strong>ercola</strong>, and <strong>mk10</strong> (not necessarily in that order) throw down a continuous two and a half hour set of glitch-filled psycheminimal techno from 25 July in Finland.','Erotus Records Kickoff Set',0,'','inherit','open','open','','110-autosave','','','2008-07-29 17:22:28','2008-07-30 00:22:28','',110,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=113',0,'revision','',0),(114,2,'2008-07-29 16:34:56','2008-07-29 23:34:56','Here\'s a live set from the guys at <a href=\"http://erotus.net\" target=\"_blank\">Erotus</a> (Blamstrain\'s new label), featured in the <a href=\"www.uudenmusiikinfestivaali.org\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Viides Uuden Musiikin Festivaali</em></a>, or \"Fifth Festival for New Music\", held in Kupittaanpuisto, Turku, Finland.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"Erotus_Records_-_Label_Launch_at_Festival_For_New_Music_5_-_25-07-2008.mp3\" target=\"_blank\">Download it</a> to hear <strong>area</strong>, <strong>asketix</strong>, <strong>blamstrain</strong>, <strong>ercola</strong>, and <strong>mk10</strong> (not necessarily in that order) throw down a continuous two and a half hour set of experimental minimal techno.','Erotus Records Kickoff Set',0,'','inherit','open','open','','110-revision-2','','','2008-07-29 16:34:56','2008-07-29 23:34:56','',110,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=114',0,'revision','',0),(115,2,'2008-07-29 20:09:13','2008-07-30 03:09:13','Having moved to the LA area little over five years ago, it wasn\'t until today that I experienced a significantly violent earthquake in our hometown of Fullerton - just across the freeway from the epicenter of the <a href=\"http://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsus/Quakes/ci14383980.php\" target=\"_blank\">5.4 quake in Chino Hills today</a>.\r\n\r\nI was talking on the phone in my studio for work, when suddenly it all started moving.\r\n\r\nWhat\'s interesting to me now is that though I remember the specific feeling of the earthquake, the adrenaline rush of anticipating when it will end, the cycles of disbelief and acceptance and small notions of what the edge of panic feels like... of all this, I remember the sounds the most.\r\n\r\nWe keep our glasses on a wire shelving unit, which began disposing victims to the kitchen floor. Not many perished, but the crashing and rattling of glass was enough to know. We also have a lot of wind chimes in various forms around different places in the house - most of which live on the front deck. The ones in my studio joined them in exultant songs of the earth! It was nothing less than enlightening, as the high timbers met the rumble of crust.\r\n\r\nWith little broken but a lot shaken (especially our cats, the breaking glass and shaking house wasn\'t their idea of a good time - though our outside cats both napped straight through), it became a sort of coming-of-age moment, as the exhilaration of an enormous power much greater than I could immediately conceive finally welcomed me to California.','The quake song',0,'','publish','open','open','','the-quake-song','','','2008-07-29 20:12:11','2008-07-30 03:12:11','',0,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=115',0,'post','',0),(116,2,'2008-07-29 20:07:30','2008-07-30 03:07:30','Having moved to southern California little over five years ago, it wasn\'t until today that I experienced a significantly violent earthquake in our hometown of Fullerton - just across the freeway from the epicenter of the 5.6 quake in Chino Hills.\n\nI was talking on the phone in my studio for work, when suddenly it all started moving. What\'s interesting to me now is that though I remember the specific feeling of the earthquake, the adrenaline rush of anticipating when it will end, the cycles of disbelief and acceptance and small notions of what the edge of panic feels like... of all this, I remember the sounds the most.\n\nWe keep our glasses on a wire shelving unit, which began disposing victims to the kitchen floor. Not many perished, but the crashing and rattling of glass was enough to know. We also have a lot of wind chimes in various forms around different places in the house - most of which live on the front deck. The ones in my studio joined them in exultant songs of the earth!\n\nWith little broken but a lot shaken (especially our cats, the breaking glass and shaking house wasn\'t their idea of a good time - though our outside cats both napped straight through), it became a sort of coming-of-age moment, as the exhilaration of an enormous power much greater than I could immediately conceive finally welcomed me to Californi','Sounds from the quake',0,'','inherit','open','open','','115-revision','','','2008-07-29 20:07:30','2008-07-30 03:07:30','',115,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=116',0,'revision','',0),(117,2,'2008-07-29 20:08:25','2008-07-30 03:08:25','Having moved to the LA area little over five years ago, it wasn\'t until today that I experienced a significantly violent earthquake in our hometown of Fullerton - just across the freeway from the epicenter of the 5.6 quake in Chino Hills.\r\n\r\nI was talking on the phone in my studio for work, when suddenly it all started moving. What\'s interesting to me now is that though I remember the specific feeling of the earthquake, the adrenaline rush of anticipating when it will end, the cycles of disbelief and acceptance and small notions of what the edge of panic feels like... of all this, I remember the sounds the most.\r\n\r\nWe keep our glasses on a wire shelving unit, which began disposing victims to the kitchen floor. Not many perished, but the crashing and rattling of glass was enough to know. We also have a lot of wind chimes in various forms around different places in the house - most of which live on the front deck. The ones in my studio joined them in exultant songs of the earth! It was nothing less than enlightening.\r\n\r\nWith little broken but a lot shaken (especially our cats, the breaking glass and shaking house wasn\'t their idea of a good time - though our outside cats both napped straight through), it became a sort of coming-of-age moment, as the exhilaration of an enormous power much greater than I could immediately conceive finally welcomed me to California.','The quake song',0,'','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-2','','','2008-07-29 20:08:25','2008-07-30 03:08:25','',115,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=117',0,'revision','',0),(118,2,'2008-07-29 20:08:55','2008-07-30 03:08:55','Having moved to the LA area little over five years ago, it wasn\'t until today that I experienced a significantly violent earthquake in our hometown of Fullerton - just across the freeway from the epicenter of the 5.6 quake in Chino Hills.\r\n\r\nI was talking on the phone in my studio for work, when suddenly it all started moving. What\'s interesting to me now is that though I remember the specific feeling of the earthquake, the adrenaline rush of anticipating when it will end, the cycles of disbelief and acceptance and small notions of what the edge of panic feels like... of all this, I remember the sounds the most.\r\n\r\nWe keep our glasses on a wire shelving unit, which began disposing victims to the kitchen floor. Not many perished, but the crashing and rattling of glass was enough to know. We also have a lot of wind chimes in various forms around different places in the house - most of which live on the front deck. The ones in my studio joined them in exultant songs of the earth! It was nothing less than enlightening.\r\n\r\nWith little broken but a lot shaken (especially our cats, the breaking glass and shaking house wasn\'t their idea of a good time - though our outside cats both napped straight through), it became a sort of coming-of-age moment, as the exhilaration of an enormous power much greater than I could immediately conceive finally welcomed me to California.','The quake song',0,'','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-3','','','2008-07-29 20:08:55','2008-07-30 03:08:55','',115,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=118',0,'revision','',0),(119,2,'2008-07-29 20:11:30','2008-07-30 03:11:30','Having moved to the LA area little over five years ago, it wasn\'t until today that I experienced a significantly violent earthquake in our hometown of Fullerton - just across the freeway from the epicenter of the <a href=\"http://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsus/Quakes/ci14383980.php\" target=\"_blank\">5.4 quake in Chino Hills today</a>.\n\nI was talking on the phone in my studio for work, when suddenly it all started moving.\n\nWhat\'s interesting to me now is that though I remember the specific feeling of the earthquake, the adrenaline rush of anticipating when it will end, the cycles of disbelief and acceptance and small notions of what the edge of panic feels like... of all this, I remember the sounds the most.\n\nWe keep our glasses on a wire shelving unit, which began disposing victims to the kitchen floor. Not many perished, but the crashing and rattling of glass was enough to know. We also have a lot of wind chimes in various forms around different places in the house - most of which live on the front deck. The ones in my studio joined them in exultant songs of the earth! It was nothing less than enlightening.\n\nWith little broken but a lot shaken (especially our cats, the breaking glass and shaking house wasn\'t their idea of a good time - though our outside cats both napped straight through), it became a sort of coming-of-age moment, as the exhilaration of an enormous power much greater than I could immediately conceive finally welcomed me to California.','The quake song',0,'','inherit','open','open','','115-autosave','','','2008-07-29 20:11:30','2008-07-30 03:11:30','',115,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=119',0,'revision','',0),(120,2,'2008-07-29 20:09:13','2008-07-30 03:09:13','Having moved to the LA area little over five years ago, it wasn\'t until today that I experienced a significantly violent earthquake in our hometown of Fullerton - just across the freeway from the epicenter of the 5.6 quake in Chino Hills.\r\n\r\nI was talking on the phone in my studio for work, when suddenly it all started moving. What\'s interesting to me now is that though I remember the specific feeling of the earthquake, the adrenaline rush of anticipating when it will end, the cycles of disbelief and acceptance and small notions of what the edge of panic feels like... of all this, I remember the sounds the most.\r\n\r\nWe keep our glasses on a wire shelving unit, which began disposing victims to the kitchen floor. Not many perished, but the crashing and rattling of glass was enough to know. We also have a lot of wind chimes in various forms around different places in the house - most of which live on the front deck. The ones in my studio joined them in exultant songs of the earth! It was nothing less than enlightening.\r\n\r\nWith little broken but a lot shaken (especially our cats, the breaking glass and shaking house wasn\'t their idea of a good time - though our outside cats both napped straight through), it became a sort of coming-of-age moment, as the exhilaration of an enormous power much greater than I could immediately conceive finally welcomed me to California.','The quake song',0,'','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-4','','','2008-07-29 20:09:13','2008-07-30 03:09:13','',115,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=120',0,'revision','',0),(121,2,'2008-07-29 17:08:02','2008-07-30 00:08:02','<strong>News and Forums</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://sonikmatter.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sonikmatter</a>: mind + music + technology</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.macmusic.org\" target=\"_blank\">MacMusic</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Editing and Analysis</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.soundhack.com/freeware.php\">Tom Erbe\'s SoundHack</a> and other assortied FFT goodies.</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.rogernicholsdigital.com/products.htm\">Roger Nichols Digital</a> has great analysis plugins, including a free one I use frequently called <a href=\"http://www.rogernicholsdigital.com/inspector.htm\">Inspector</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.klingbeil.com/spear/\">SPEAR</a> (Sinusoidal Partial Editing Analysis and Resynthesis) is a fairly new and promising, with some very neato graphic tools</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.hairersoft.com\">Amadeus Pro</a> is one of the better low-priced audio editors out there.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.sonicvisualiser.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Sonic Visualiser</a> is a graphical interface for sound file analysis.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Modular Music Making</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://cycling74.com/\">Cycling 74</a> is the home of the ubiquitous <a href=\"http://cycling74.com/products/maxmsp\">Max/MSP</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://puredata.info/\" target=\"_blank\">PureData</a> (PD) \"is a real-time graphical programming environment for audio, video, and graphical processing\" - what amounts to the \"free\" version of Max/MSP, as it is all based on code by the same guy (Miller Puckette)</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://plogue.com/\">Plogue Bidule</a> is a max/msp-like audio manipulator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Plug-in Tech</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://mda.smartelectronix.com/\">MDA Effects</a> are some of the coolest free plugins out there.</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://destroyfx.smartelectronix.com/\">Destroy FX</a> is a nice (free) suite of simple yet effective plug-ins for granular processing and spectral effects.</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://cycling74.com/products/pluggo\">Pluggo</a> is a superb and inexpensive collection of great Max/MSP plugins</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.audiodamage.com\">Audio Damage</a> has some very nice sounding simple low cost effects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Stand-Alone Synthesis</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.spongefork.com/3/\">Spongefork</a> : really neat graphical noisemaker for MacOSX</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://minicomputer.sourceforge.net/\">Minicomputer</a> : simple digital synthesizer for Linux</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.bitminds.net/kymatica/index.php/Software/AlgoScore\">AlgoScore</a> : \"graphical environment for algorithmic composition\" for <span class=\"twikiNewLink\">MacOSX<a title=\"Create this topic\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"/bin/edit/Main/MacOSX?topicparent=Main.AudioSoftware\">?</a></span> (includes source code so it could be portable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Sampling and Looping</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://plasq.com/musolomo/\">Musolomo</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>OS Specific</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.pure-mac.com/audio.html\">PureMac Music Software Listing</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Audio Software',0,'','inherit','open','open','','89-revision-4','','','2008-07-29 17:08:02','2008-07-30 00:08:02','',89,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=121',0,'revision','',0),(1136,2,'2019-08-20 16:21:16','2019-08-20 23:21:16','My instruments and electronics, and links that matter to them... still building this list very slowly with pictures to boot, but I have a lot of shit.\n\nBehringer\n<ul>\n 	<li>Xenyx1622FX Mixer</li>\n 	<li>Truth B2031 nearfield Monitors</li>\n</ul>\nDIY &amp; Crafted\n<ul>\n 	<li>Thingamakit</li>\n 	<li>Cookie Monster</li>\n</ul>\nLooping, Sampling, Delays\n<ul>\n 	<li>Boss PS-3 Pitch Shifter / Delay</li>\n 	<li>Line6 DL4 Delay Modeler</li>\n 	<li>Electrix Repeater</li>\n 	<li>Electrix MoFX</li>\n 	<li>DigiTech TimeMachine RDS4000</li>\n</ul>','Musical Arsenal',0,'','inherit','closed','closed','','314-revision-v1','','','2019-08-20 16:21:16','2019-08-20 23:21:16','',314,'https://sounding.com/blog/2019/08/20/314-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1137,2,'2019-08-20 16:24:13','2019-08-20 23:24:13','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I recycle things to build more things that are sometimes good for things and sometimes not. I haven\'t done any of these in a while.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[nggallery id=1]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Sculpture',0,'','inherit','closed','closed','','387-revision-v1','','','2019-08-20 16:24:13','2019-08-20 23:24:13','',387,'https://sounding.com/blog/2019/08/20/387-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(799,2,'2012-04-18 10:32:01','2012-04-18 17:32:01','DIY Electronics\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All kinds of modulars and parts for sale at <a href=\"http://analoguehaven.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Analogue Haven</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.anti-theory.com/soundart/circuitbend/\" target=\"_blank\">Circuit-Bending Howto</a> at Anti-Theory.com</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.getlofi.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GetLoFi</a> Circuit Bending Synth DIY: \"Circuit Bending tips and resources for Beginners and Pros alike.\"</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.musicfromouterspace.com/analogsynth.php?page=ANALOG\">Music from Outer Space</a> has analog synth examples and resources.</li>\r\n	<li>Georgia Tech has lectures and coursework online for Aaron Lanterman\'s <a href=\"http://users.ece.gatech.edu/~lanterma/ems/\" target=\"_blank\">Electronics for Music Synthesis</a> class.</li>\r\n	<li>MIT\'s online <a href=\"http://ocw.mit.edu/OcwWeb/Electrical-Engineering-and-Computer-Science/6-002Spring-2007/CourseHome/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Circuits and Electronics</a> course.</li>\r\n	<li>Eric Archer and his amazing <a href=\"http://ericarcher.net/devices/\" target=\"_blank\">retro-fitted prototypes and sonic circuitry</a></li>\r\n	<li>The little known hardware hacking of <a href=\"http://www.sdiy.org/knas\" target=\"_blank\">Knas</a></li>\r\n	<li>Erik Hansen has some interesting <a href=\"http://www.erikhansen.net/?page_id=22\" target=\"_blank\">mods for guitar pedals</a></li>\r\n	<li>AMZ <a href=\"http://www.muzique.com/schem/projects.htm\" target=\"_blank\">effects project schematics</a></li>\r\n	<li>Music From Outer Space <a href=\"http://www.musicfromouterspace.com/analogsynth/YOUR_FIRST_SYNTH/WSG_Reborn/WEIRDSOUNDGENERATORREBORN.php\" target=\"_blank\">Weird Noise Generator</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPCB modules\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.arduino.cc/\" target=\"_blank\">Arduino</a> \"is an open-source electronics prototyping platform\" whereby users can insert software code onto an outboard chipset to make custom hardware effects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\"Pad\" (MIDI) controllers\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.c-thru-music.com/cgi/?page=prod_axis-64\" target=\"_blank\">AXis-64</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://lividinstruments.com/hardware_ohm.php\">Livid OHM</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/ctm.htm\">Doepfer CTM</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://monome.org/series/\">Monome</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.global.yamaha.com/tenori-on\">Yamaha Tenori-On</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.zendrum.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Zendrum</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nModular Devices\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://eurorackdb.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Eurorack Database</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/\" target=\"_blank\">Doepfer</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://analoguehaven.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Analogue Haven</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.modularsynth.com/chart.html\" target=\"_blank\">Modular Synth Comparison Chart</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/apr09/articles/goingmodular.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Guide to Choosing a Modular Synth</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.synthesizers.com/formfactors.html\" target=\"_blank\">Modular Synth Form Factors</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.muffwiggler.com/forum\" target=\"_blank\">Muff Wiggler Forum</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.stefanbreitenfeld.com/modularplanner.php\" target=\"_blank\">Modular Planner</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTheremins\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.thereminworld.com\" target=\"_blank\">Theremin World</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Audio Hardware',0,'','inherit','open','open','','90-revision-21','','','2012-04-18 10:32:01','2012-04-18 17:32:01','',90,'http://sounding.com/blog/2012/04/18/90-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(798,2,'2011-12-15 22:58:21','2011-12-16 06:58:21','DIY Electronics\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All kinds of modulars and parts for sale at <a href=\"http://analoguehaven.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Analogue Haven</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.anti-theory.com/soundart/circuitbend/\" target=\"_blank\">Circuit-Bending Howto</a> at Anti-Theory.com</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.getlofi.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GetLoFi</a> Circuit Bending Synth DIY: \"Circuit Bending tips and resources for Beginners and Pros alike.\"</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.musicfromouterspace.com/analogsynth.php?page=ANALOG\">Music from Outer Space</a> has analog synth examples and resources.</li>\r\n	<li>Georgia Tech has lectures and coursework online for Aaron Lanterman\'s <a href=\"http://users.ece.gatech.edu/~lanterma/ems/\" target=\"_blank\">Electronics for Music Synthesis</a> class.</li>\r\n	<li>MIT\'s online <a href=\"http://ocw.mit.edu/OcwWeb/Electrical-Engineering-and-Computer-Science/6-002Spring-2007/CourseHome/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Circuits and Electronics</a> course.</li>\r\n	<li>Eric Archer and his amazing <a href=\"http://ericarcher.net/devices/\" target=\"_blank\">retro-fitted prototypes and sonic circuitry</a></li>\r\n	<li>The little known hardware hacking of <a href=\"http://www.sdiy.org/knas\" target=\"_blank\">Knas</a></li>\r\n	<li>Erik Hansen has some interesting <a href=\"http://www.erikhansen.net/?page_id=22\" target=\"_blank\">mods for guitar pedals</a></li>\r\n	<li>AMZ <a href=\"http://www.muzique.com/schem/projects.htm\" target=\"_blank\">effects project schematics</a></li>\r\n	<li>Music From Outer Space <a href=\"http://www.musicfromouterspace.com/analogsynth/YOUR_FIRST_SYNTH/WSG_Reborn/WEIRDSOUNDGENERATORREBORN.php\" target=\"_blank\">Weird Noise Generator</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPCB modules\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.arduino.cc/\" target=\"_blank\">Arduino</a> \"is an open-source electronics prototyping platform\" whereby users can insert software code onto an outboard chipset to make custom hardware effects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\"Pad\" (MIDI) controllers\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.c-thru-music.com/cgi/?page=prod_axis-64\" target=\"_blank\">AXis-64</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://lividinstruments.com/hardware_ohm.php\">Livid OHM</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/ctm.htm\">Doepfer CTM</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://monome.org/series/\">Monome</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.global.yamaha.com/tenori-on\">Yamaha Tenori-On</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.zendrum.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Zendrum</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nModular Devices\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/\" target=\"_blank\">Doepfer</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.serge-fans.com/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Serge</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://analoguehaven.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Analogue Haven</a> is the exclusive North American reseller for Doepfer.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://synthesizers.com\" target=\"_blank\">Synthesizers.com</a> makes very similar devices to the Doepfer system, at a comparable price.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ken Stone\'s Modular designs</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.modularsynth.com/chart.html\" target=\"_blank\">Modular Synth Comparison Chart</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/apr09/articles/goingmodular.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Guide to Choosing a Modular Synth</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.synthesizers.com/formfactors.html\" target=\"_blank\">Modular Synth Form Factors</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.muffwiggler.com/forum\" target=\"_blank\">Muff Wiggler Forum</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.stefanbreitenfeld.com/modularplanner.php\" target=\"_blank\">Modular Planner</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTheremins\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.thereminworld.com\" target=\"_blank\">Theremin World</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Audio Hardware',0,'','inherit','open','open','','90-revision-20','','','2011-12-15 22:58:21','2011-12-16 06:58:21','',90,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/12/15/90-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(123,2,'2008-07-06 16:46:45','2008-07-06 23:46:45','<h2>\"Pad\" controllers</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://lividinstruments.com/hardware_ohm.php\">Livid OHM</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/ctm.htm\">Doepfer CTM</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://monome.org/series/\">Monome</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.global.yamaha.com/tenori-on\">Yamaha Tenori-On</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Modular Devices</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/\">Doepfer</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://analoguehaven.com/\">Analogue Haven</a> is the exclusive North American reseller for Doepfer.</li>\r\n</ul>','Audio Hardware',0,'','inherit','open','open','','90-revision','','','2008-07-06 16:46:45','2008-07-06 23:46:45','',90,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=123',0,'revision','',0),(124,2,'2008-08-02 11:00:56','2008-08-02 18:00:56','<a href=\"http://www.anti-theory.com/soundart/\" target=\"_blank\">Sound Art at Anti-Theory.com</a> professes to be where \"the art of circuit-bending was launched on the internet,\" and it\'s actually a nice resource for getting into avant-garde uses of musical toys.\r\n\r\nIn <a href=\"http://www.anti-theory.com/soundart/circuitbend/cb06.html\" target=\"_blank\">[how it works]</a> a step-by-step example shows the simple circuit-bending process, and other topics go into things like tools and equipment and advanced things about electronics.','Getting into Circuit-Bending?',0,'','publish','open','open','','getting-into-circuit-bending','','','2008-08-02 11:00:56','2008-08-02 18:00:56','',0,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=124',0,'post','',0),(125,2,'2008-08-02 11:00:49','2008-08-02 18:00:49','<a href=\"http://www.anti-theory.com/soundart/\" target=\"_blank\">Sound Art at Anti-Theory.com</a> professes to be where \"the art of circuit-bending was launched on the internet,\" and it\'s actually a nice resource for getting into avant-garde uses of musical toys.\n\nIn <a href=\"http://www.anti-theory.com/soundart/circuitbend/cb06.html\" target=\"_blank\">[how it works]</a> a step-by-step example shows the simple circuit-bending process, and other topics go into things like tools and equipment and advanced things about electronics.','Getting into Circuit-Bending?',0,'','inherit','open','open','','124-revision','','','2008-08-02 11:00:49','2008-08-02 18:00:49','',124,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=125',0,'revision','',0),(126,2,'2008-07-30 13:17:22','2008-07-30 20:17:22','DIY Electronics\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.musicfromouterspace.com/analogsynth.php?page=ANALOG\">Music from Outer Space</a> has analog synth examples and resources.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\"Pad\" controllers\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://lividinstruments.com/hardware_ohm.php\">Livid OHM</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/ctm.htm\">Doepfer CTM</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://monome.org/series/\">Monome</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.global.yamaha.com/tenori-on\">Yamaha Tenori-On</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nModular Devices\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/\">Doepfer</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://analoguehaven.com/\">Analogue Haven</a> is the exclusive North American reseller for Doepfer.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://synthesizers.com\" target=\"_blank\">Synthesizers.com</a> makes very similar devices to the Doepfer system, at a comparable price.</li>\r\n</ul>','Audio Hardware',0,'','inherit','open','open','','90-revision-2','','','2008-07-30 13:17:22','2008-07