embers of the electronic music community whose work I highly respect. Not only is most of his software free, not only are they usable by any skill level, not only are they the most educational electronic music tools i\'ve ever used... I could go on. But the end result is that they sound simple and great.\r\n\r\nAt long last Tom has released the <a href=\"http://www.soundhack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SoundHack Delay Trio</a>, the description of the algorithms is fantastic, from the announcement:\r\n<blockquote>\"All of these are derived from the same basic delay algorithm: a hermite interpolated delay line with variable modulation, and a feedback loop with dc blocking and saturation. Pitch shifting is achieved with a dual head crossfading delay (ala Eltro Tempophon/Dennis Gabor/Pierre Schaeffer phonogene) and is decidedly low-ﬁ. The saturating feedback also allows them to be great drone and noise generators.\"</blockquote>\r\nAwesome work! Can\'t wait to get this one in action, I have something going now that begs for some new delay. ;)\r\n\r\nTwo of my other favorites of Tom\'s are <strong>decimate+</strong> and of course the ubiquitous <strong>SoundHack</strong>, both available (along with a TON of others) on the <a href=\"http://www.soundhack.com/freeware.php\" target=\"_blank\">SoundHack Freeware page</a>.','SoundHack Delay Trio Released',0,'','inherit','open','open','','150-revision-4','','','2008-09-03 15:55:22','2008-09-03 22:55:22','',150,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=155',0,'revision','',0),(156,2,'2008-08-29 12:17:03','2008-08-29 19:17:03','DIY Electronics\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.anti-theory.com/soundart/circuitbend/\" target=\"_blank\">Circuit-Bending Howto</a> at Anti-Theory.com</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.getlofi.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GetLoFi</a> Circuit Bending Synth DIY: \"Circuit Bending tips and resources for Beginners and Pros alike.\"</li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.musicfromouterspace.com/analogsynth.php?page=ANALOG\">Music from Outer Space</a> has analog synth examples and resources.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPCB modules\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.arduino.cc/\" target=\"_blank\">Arduino</a> \"is an open-source electronics prototyping platform\" whereby users can insert software code onto an outboard chipset to make custom hardware effects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\"Pad\" (MIDI) controllers\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.c-thru-music.com/cgi/?page=prod_axis-64\" target=\"_blank\">AXis-64</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://lividinstruments.com/hardware_ohm.php\">Livid OHM</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/ctm.htm\">Doepfer CTM</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://monome.org/series/\">Monome</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.global.yamaha.com/tenori-on\">Yamaha Tenori-On</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.zendrum.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Zendrum</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nModular Devices\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/\">Doepfer</a></li>\r\n	<li> <a href=\"http://analoguehaven.com/\">Analogue Haven</a> is the exclusive North American reseller for Doepfer.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://synthesizers.com\" target=\"_blank\">Synthesizers.com</a> makes very similar devices to the Doepfer system, at a comparable price.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTheremins\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.thereminworld.com\" target=\"_blank\">Theremin World</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Audio Hardware',0,'','inherit','open','open','','90-revision-7','','','2008-08-29 12:17:03','2008-08-29 19:17:03','',90,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=156',0,'revision','',0),(157,2,'2008-10-02 18:54:44','2008-10-03 01:54:44','In 2001 the debut 12\" for Craque titled <strong>Trolling for Olives EP</strong> was released on <a href=\"http://www.discogs.com/label/Metatron+Press\" target=\"_blank\">Metatron Press</a>, and now it\'s <a href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/Craque/Trolling+for+Olives+EP\" target=\"_blank\">available for free on last.fm</a>.\r\n\r\nAll five tracks are both streamable and downloadable, I figur