ing about this page is the wiring schematic at the very bottom on how to wire busses to pots.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://sound.westhost.com/project129.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://sound.westhost.com/project129.htm</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis FET style mixer is basically a step up from a passive mixer with no buffers, sometimes used in place of an OpAmp:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.aaroncake.net/circuits/mixer1.asp\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.aaroncake.net/circuits/mixer1.asp</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese are a selection of good starting points for learning how to build input/output buffers, focused mostly on JFET, but with some discussion of JFET OpAmps:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.muzique.com/lab/buffers.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.muzique.com/lab/buffers.htm</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nKen Stone\'s well known mixer designs. PCB\'s are no longer available, but the theory and technique is there:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Matrix Mixer: <a href=\"http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs33_matrix_mixer.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs33_matrix_mixer.html</a></li>\r\n	<li>\"DC\" Mixer: <a href=\"http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs04_mix.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs04_mix.html</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe Doepfer A-100 DIY Matrix Mixer example schematic (about halfway down the page):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/DIY/a100_diy.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.doepfer.de/DIY/a100_diy.htm</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe <strong>Bucha Matrix Mixer Clone</strong> thread at Electro-Music contains <strong>vtl5c3\'s </strong>posts about his 8x8 project, which follows the Buchla design. The only place I\'ve been able to find the Buchla schematic online, and has great photos of the mixer\'s guts:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://electro-music.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27275\" target=\"_blank\">http://electro-music.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27275</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>UPDATE:</strong>\r\n\r\n<e