f the better links I\'ve uncovered that are useful for getting your head around the entire idea of designing a matrix mixer.\r\n\r\nA lot of good guidance here, using OmAmps for buffering, though I think the best thing about this page is the nice wiring schematic at the very bottom on how to wire buses.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://sound.westhost.com/project129.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://sound.westhost.com/project129.htm</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis JFET style mixer is basically a step up from a passive mixer with no buffers, sometimes used in place of an OpAmp:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.aaroncake.net/circuits/mixer1.asp\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.aaroncake.net/circuits/mixer1.asp</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese are a selection of great starting points for learning how to build simple input/output buffers, focused mostly on JFET, but with some discussion of JFET OpAmps:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.muzique.com/lab/buffers.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.muzique.com/lab/buffers.htm</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nKen Stone\'s well known mixer designs. PCB\'s are no longer available, but the theory and technique is there:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Matrix Mixer: <a href=\"http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs33_matrix_mixer.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs33_matrix_mixer.html</a></li>\r\n	<li>\"DC\" Mixer: <a href=\"http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs04_mix.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.cgs.synth.net/modules/cgs04_mix.html</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe Doepfer A-100 DIY Matrix Mixer example schematic (about halfway down the page):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.doepfer.de/DIY/a100_diy.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.doepfer.de/DIY/a100_diy.htm</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe <strong>Bucha Matrix Mixer Clone</strong> thread at Electro-Music contains <strong>vtl5c3\'s </strong>posts about his 8x8 project, which follows the Buchla design. The only place I\'ve been able to find the Buchla schematic online, and has great photos of the mixer\'s guts:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://electro-music.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27275\" target=\"_blank\">http://electro-music.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27275</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>UPDATE:</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>I\'ve breadboarded the input/output stages with NTE451 JFET\'s using a 50k pot and 56k \'mixing\' resistors, I think I\'ve found the perfect combination out of parts I already own... I need to swing by Orvac later today and possibly pick up more transistors and resistors so I can build the protoboard. -mrd 20110411</em>','Matrix Mixering',0,'','inherit','open','open','','415-revision-12','','','2011-04-11 14:57:01','2011-04-11 21:57:01','',415,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/04/11/415-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(439,2,'2011-08-31 11:01:36','2011-08-31 18:01:36','Just in case you missed it, SoundWalk Long Beach 2011 is just around the corner! Check out the newly posted set of mp3\'s from last year\'s event at <a href=\"http://craque.net\" target=\"_blank\">craque.net</a> (or <a href=\"http://craque.net/snd/swlbc/soundwalk2010_flac.zip\">download a zip file of flac files</a> directly).\r\n\r\nHere\'s a couple of pix from last year\'s event...\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_444\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\" caption=\"Craque performing at SoundWalk 2010 in Long Beach, CA\"]<a href=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_playing.jpg\"><img src=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_playing-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"craque_sw2010_playing\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-444\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_445\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"225\" caption=\"Dave doubles as stagehand and soundmaker improvisor\"]<a href=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_dave2.jpg\"><img src=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_dave2-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"craque_sw2010_dave2\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-445\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_446\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"225\" caption=\"Later in the evening, up close with participants\"]<a href=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_joined.jpg\"><img src=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_joined-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"craque_sw2010_joined\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-446\" /></a>[/caption]','SoundWalk 2011 is coming',0,'','publish','open','open','','soundwalk-2011-is-coming','','','2011-09-03 16:21:30','2011-09-03 23:21:30','',0,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=439',0,'post','',0),(431,2,'2011-06-22 23:52:13','2011-06-23 06:52:13','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"425\" height=\"349\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/G6ilKVeP7k0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n\r\nTo be done on this prototype:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\r\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\r\n	<li>CV input</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI went through quite a few opamps before finally deciding on the dual jfets, and now I really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\r\n\r\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\r\n\r\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a follower/buffer and a high-gain resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\r\n\r\nExcited to have this core design done, LOVE playing with it! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion.','\"Booglitchoo\" Synth Prototype',0,'','publish','open','open','','booglitchoo-synth-prototype','','','2011-06-22 23:52:13','2011-06-23 06:52:13','',0,'http://sounding.com/blog/?p=431',0,'post','',0),(432,2,'2011-06-22 23:44:37','2011-06-23 06:44:37','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\n\nTo be done on this prototype:\n<ol>\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\n	<li>CV input</li>\n</ol>\nI went through quite a few opamps before coming upon the dual jfets and really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\n\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\n\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a buffer and a resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\n\nExcited to have this core done, especially the opamp choice! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion of what\'s shaping up to be an awesome sound.','\"Booglitchoo\" analog ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','431-revision','','','2011-06-22 23:44:37','2011-06-23 06:44:37','',431,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/06/22/431-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(433,2,'2011-06-22 23:45:44','2011-06-23 06:45:44','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo be done on this prototype:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\r\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\r\n	<li>CV input</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI went through quite a few opamps before coming upon the dual jfets and really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\r\n\r\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\r\n\r\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a buffer and a resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\r\n\r\nExcited to have this core done, especially the opamp choice! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion of what\'s shaping up to be an awesome sound.','\"Booglitchoo\" analog ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','431-revision-2','','','2011-06-22 23:45:44','2011-06-23 06:45:44','',431,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/06/22/431-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(435,2,'2011-06-22 23:48:39','2011-06-23 06:48:39','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo be done on this prototype:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\r\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\r\n	<li>CV input</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI went through quite a few opamps before finally deciding on the dual jfets, and now I really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\r\n\r\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\r\n\r\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a follower/buffer and a high-gain resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\r\n\r\nExcited to have this core design done, LOVE playing with it! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion.','\"Booglitchoo\" analog ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','431-revision-4','','','2011-06-22 23:48:39','2011-06-23 06:48:39','',431,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/06/22/431-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(434,2,'2011-06-22 23:48:09','2011-06-23 06:48:09','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTo be done on this prototype:\n<ol>\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\n	<li>CV input</li>\n</ol>\nI went through quite a few opamps before finally deciding on the dual jfets, and now I really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\n\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\n\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a follower/buffer and a high-gain resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\n\nExcited to have this core done, especially the opamp choice! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion of what\'s shaping up to be an awesome sound.','\"Booglitchoo\" analog ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','431-revision-3','','','2011-06-22 23:48:09','2011-06-23 06:48:09','',431,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/06/22/431-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(436,2,'2011-06-22 23:49:26','2011-06-23 06:49:26','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"425\" height=\"349\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/G6ilKVeP7k0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n\r\nTo be done on this prototype:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\r\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\r\n	<li>CV input</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI went through quite a few opamps before finally deciding on the dual jfets, and now I really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\r\n\r\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\r\n\r\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a follower/buffer and a high-gain resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\r\n\r\nExcited to have this core design done, LOVE playing with it! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion.','\"Booglitchoo\" analog ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','431-revision-5','','','2011-06-22 23:49:26','2011-06-23 06:49:26','',431,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/06/22/431-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(437,2,'2011-06-22 23:49:43','2011-06-23 06:49:43','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"425\" height=\"349\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/G6ilKVeP7k0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n\r\nTo be done on this prototype:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\r\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\r\n	<li>CV input</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI went through quite a few opamps before finally deciding on the dual jfets, and now I really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\r\n\r\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\r\n\r\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a follower/buffer and a high-gain resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\r\n\r\nExcited to have this core design done, LOVE playing with it! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion.','\"Booglitchoo\" analog ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','431-revision-6','','','2011-06-22 23:49:43','2011-06-23 06:49:43','',431,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/06/22/431-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(438,2,'2011-06-22 23:51:17','2011-06-23 06:51:17','Here we go... I\'ve optimized the way I\'m using power, love the way the dual jfet opamps (TL082) sound, and have the mixing elements mostly decided.\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"425\" height=\"349\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/G6ilKVeP7k0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n\r\nTo be done on this prototype:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>use either capacitor switching or a simple 4017 sequencer to change up the textural possibilities of the oscillator</li>\r\n	<li>add switches to the voice modulator to allow for \"skipping around\" pitches instead of only up or down changes</li>\r\n	<li>CV input</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI went through quite a few opamps before finally deciding on the dual jfets, and now I really dig how they\'re working with the complex waveform of the four NAND gates (NTE4093)... I use it first as a multipole low-pass filter to shape the sound of the chained oscillators.\r\n\r\nBecause of the nature of the sounds I don\'t find much use for the vibrato section of the voice modulator (HT8950), but don\'t mind at all because it reduces the component count and I\'m finding an incredible amount of possibilities already. You\'ll also notice I\'m using my fingers on a couple of resistors to change the pitch... I discovered this by accident, but really like the gestural aspect of it so much that I\'m planning on building a touch interface into the final design. :)\r\n\r\nThe whole thing is finally mixed into another dual opamp, with a follower/buffer and a high-gain resonant Q notch filter to add some harmonics and really cool sweep possibilities.\r\n\r\nExcited to have this core design done, LOVE playing with it! Now it\'s just a matter tweaking and expansion.','\"Booglitchoo\" Synth Prototype',0,'','inherit','open','open','','431-revision-7','','','2011-06-22 23:51:17','2011-06-23 06:51:17','',431,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/06/22/431-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(440,2,'2011-07-01 16:19:02','2011-07-01 23:19:02','','Auto Draft',0,'','inherit','open','open','','439-revision','','','2011-07-01 16:19:02','2011-07-01 23:19:02','',439,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/07/01/439-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(442,2,'2011-08-31 11:00:59','2011-08-31 18:00:59','Just in case you missed it, SoundWalk Long Beach 2011 is just around the corner! I\'ve updated <a href=\"http://craque.net\" target=\"_blank\">craque.net</a> with some excerpts from last year\'s outing - unfortunately there were some recording mishaps and these three shortish excerpts are the best sections salvaged.\n\nOr if you\'re the remixing/audiophile type, <a href=\"http://craque.net/snd/swlbc/craque-soundwalk2010-flac.zip\">download the zip of FLACs</a>.','SoundWalk 2011 is coming',0,'','inherit','open','open','','439-revision-2','','','2011-08-31 11:00:59','2011-08-31 18:00:59','',439,'http://sounding.com/blog/2011/08/31/439-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(443,2,'2011-09-03 16:20:38','2011-09-03 23:20:38','Just in case you missed it, SoundWalk Long Beach 2011 is just around the corner! Check out the newly posted set of mp3\'s from last year\'s event at http://craque.net (or download a zip file of flac files directly).\n\nHere\'s a couple of pix from last year\'s event...\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_444\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\" caption=\"Craque performing at SoundWalk 2010 in Long Beach, CA\"]<a href=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_playing.jpg\"><img src=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_playing-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"craque_sw2010_playing\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-444\" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_445\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"225\" caption=\"Dave doubles as stagehand and soundmaker improvisor\"]<a href=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_dave2.jpg\"><img src=\"https://sounding.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/craque_sw2010_dave2-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"craque_sw2010_dave2\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-445\" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption 